<font color="#FF0000">RE: DRUG USE IN VIETNAM</font><br>
<tt>Sat Aug  2 12:45:46 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I was stationed in Duc Trong in the central Highlands in 69 &amp; 70. part of C Co 577th Engineers. We were attached to a Fire base and a MACV outpost. I can only speak of my own experience, which was one of almost non stop drug and alcohol use and abuse. Any type of drug could be purchased <br>
openly.All you had to do to buy prescription type drugs,<br>
such &quot;reds&quot; &amp; &quot;Black beauties&quot; was go to a pharmacy and point to what you wanted. Opium could be purchased at the local &quot;opium den&quot; to be smoked there or to go. Marijauna was cheap and plentiful. And the choices of alcohol off base <br>
went from the mundane,beers such as 33 to the excotic such as rice wines and home brewed wiskeys with flower petal floating in the mixture. I would estimate that practically evreyone used something to numb themselves.
